M|prioritization-advisor|Guide product managers in choosing the right prioritization framework by asking adaptive questions about product stage, team ctx, dec-making needs, and stakeholder dynamics. Use this to avoid "framewo
M|prioritization-advisor|This is not a scoring calculator—it's a dec guide that matches prioritization frameworks to your specific situation.
M|prioritization-advisor|Common frameworks and when to use them:
M|prioritization-advisor|**Scoring frameworks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|- **RICE** (Reach, Impact, Confidence, Effort) — Data-driven, requires metrics
M|prioritization-advisor|- **ICE** (Impact, Confidence, Ease) — Lightweight, gut-check scoring
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Value vs. Effort** (2x2 matrix) — Quick wins vs. strategic bets
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Weighted Scoring** — Custom criteria with stakeholder input
M|prioritization-advisor|**Strategic frameworks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Kano Model** — Classify features by customer delight (basic, performance, delight)
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Opportunity Scoring** — Rate importance vs. satisfaction gap
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Buy-a-Feature** — Customer budget allocation exercise
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Moscow** (Must, Should, Could, Won't) — Forcing function for hard choices
M|prioritization-advisor|**Contextual frameworks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Cost of Delay** — Urgency-based (time-sensitive features)
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Impact Mapping** — Goal-driven (tie features to outcomes)
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Story Mapping** — User journey-based (narrative flow)
M|prioritization-advisor|- **ctx-aware:** Matches framework to product stage, team maturity, data availability
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Anti-dogmatic:** No single "best" framework—it depends on your situation
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Actionable:** Provides implementation steps, not just framework names
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Not a universal ranking:** Frameworks aren't "better" or "worse"—they fit different contexts
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Not a replacement for str:** Frameworks execute str; they don't create it
M|prioritization-advisor|- **Not set-it-and-forget-it:** Reassess frameworks as your product matures
M|prioritization-advisor|- Choosing a prioritization framework for the first time
M|prioritization-advisor|- Switching frameworks (current one isn't working)
M|prioritization-advisor|- Aligning stakeholders on prioritization process
M|prioritization-advisor|- Onboarding new PMs to team practices
M|prioritization-advisor|- When you already have a working framework (don't fix what isn't broken)
M|prioritization-advisor|- For one-off decisions (frameworks are for recurring prioritization)
M|prioritization-advisor|- As a substitute for strategic vision (frameworks can't tell you what to build)
M|prioritization-advisor|Use [`workshop-facilitation`](../workshop-facilitation/SKILL.md) as the default interaction protocol for this skill.
M|prioritization-advisor|It defines:
M|prioritization-advisor|- ses heads-up + entry mode (Guided, ctx dump, Best guess)
M|prioritization-advisor|- one-question turns with plain-language prompts
M|prioritization-advisor|- progress labels (for example, ctx Qx/8 and Scoring Qx/5)
M|prioritization-advisor|- interruption handling and pause/resume behavior
M|prioritization-advisor|- numbered recommendations at dec points
M|prioritization-advisor|- quick-select numbered rsp options for regular questions (include `Other (specify)` when useful)
M|prioritization-advisor|This file defines the domain-specific assessment cnt. If there is a conflict, follow this file's domain logic.
M|prioritization-advisor|This interactive skill asks **up to 4 adaptive questions**, offering **3-4 enumerated options** at each step.
M|prioritization-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|"What stage is your product in?"
M|prioritization-advisor|**Offer 4 enumerated options:**
M|prioritization-advisor|1. **Pre-product/market fit** — "Searching for PMF; experimenting rapidly; unclear what customers want" (High uncertainty, need speed)
M|prioritization-advisor|2. **Early PMF, scaling** — "Found initial PMF; growing fast; adding features to retain/expand" (Moderate uncertainty, balancing speed + quality)
M|prioritization-advisor|3. **Mature product, optimization** — "Established market; incremental improvements; competing on quality/features" (Low uncertainty, data-driven decisions)
M|prioritization-advisor|4. **Multiple products/platform** — "Portfolio of products; cross-product dependencies; complex stakeholder needs" (Coordination complexity)
M|prioritization-advisor|**Or describe your product stage (new idea, growth mode, established, etc.).**
M|prioritization-advisor|**User rsp:** [Selection or custom]
M|prioritization-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|"What's your team and stakeholder environment like?"
M|prioritization-advisor|**Offer 4 enumerated options:**
M|prioritization-advisor|1. **Small team, limited resources** — "3-5 engineers, 1 PM, need to focus ruthlessly" (Need simple, fast framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|2. **Cross-functional team, aligned** — "Product, design, engineering aligned; clear goals; good collaboration" (Can use data-driven frameworks)
M|prioritization-advisor|3. **Multiple stakeholders, misaligned** — "Execs, sales, customers all have opinions; need transparent process" (Need consensus-building framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|4. **Large org, complex dependencies** — "Multiple teams, shared roadmap, cross-team dependencies" (Need coordination framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|**Or describe your team/stakeholder ctx.**
M|prioritization-advisor|**User rsp:** [Selection or custom]
M|prioritization-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|"What's the primary challenge you're trying to solve with prioritization?"
M|prioritization-advisor|**Offer 4 enumerated options:**
M|prioritization-advisor|1. **Too many ideas, unclear which to pursue** — "Backlog is 100+ items; need to narrow to top 10" (Need filtering framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|2. **Stakeholders disagree on priorities** — "Sales wants features, execs want strategic bets, engineering wants tech debt" (Need alignment framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|3. **Lack of data-driven decisions** — "Prioritizing by gut feel; want metrics-based process" (Need scoring framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|4. **Hard tradeoffs between strategic bets vs. quick wins** — "Balancing long-term vision vs. short-term customer needs" (Need value/effort framework)
M|prioritization-advisor|**Or describe your specific challenge.**
M|prioritization-advisor|**User rsp:** [Selection or custom]
M|prioritization-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|prioritization-advisor|"How much data do you have to inform prioritization?"
M|prioritization-advisor|**Offer 3 enumerated options:**
M|prioritization-advisor|1. **Minimal data** — "New product, no usage metrics, few customers to survey" (Gut-based frameworks)
M|prioritization-advisor|2. **Some data** — "Basic anl, customer feedback, but no rigorous data collection" (Lightweight scoring frameworks)
M|prioritization-advisor|3. **Rich data** — "Usage metrics, A/B tests, customer surveys, clear success metrics" (Data-driven frameworks)
M|prioritization-advisor|**Or describe your data situation.**
M|prioritization-advisor|**User rsp:** [Selection or custom]
M|prioritization-advisor|After collecting responses, the agt recommends a framework:
M|prioritization-advisor|```markdown
